sec-aggregate-error-constructor.name: AggregateError
sec-aggregate-error-constructor.summary: The AggregateError() constructor creates AggregateError objects.
sec-aggregate-error-constructor.title: AggregateError() constructor

sec-aggregate-error.name: errors
sec-aggregate-error.summary: The errors data property of an AggregateError instance contains an array representing the errors that were aggregated.
sec-aggregate-error.title: AggregateError: errors

sec-aggregate-error-objects.name: AggregateError
sec-aggregate-error-objects.summary: The AggregateError object represents an error when several errors need to be wrapped in a single error. It is thrown when multiple errors need to be reported by an operation, for example by Promise.any(), when all promises passed to it reject.
sec-aggregate-error-objects.title: AggregateError

sec-array-constructor.name: Array
sec-array-constructor.summary: The Array() constructor creates Array objects.
sec-array-constructor.title: Array() constructor

sec-array.prototype.at.name: at
sec-array.prototype.at.summary: The at() method takes an integer value and returns the item at that index, allowing for positive and negative integers. Negative integers count back from the last item in the array.
sec-array.prototype.at.title: Array.prototype.at()

sec-array.prototype.concat.name: concat
sec-array.prototype.concat.summary: The concat() method is used to merge two or more arrays. This method does not change the existing arrays, but instead returns a new array.
sec-array.prototype.concat.title: Array.prototype.concat()

sec-array.prototype.copywithin.name: copyWithin
sec-array.prototype.copywithin.summary: The copyWithin() method shallow copies part of an array to another location in the same array and returns it without modifying its length.
sec-array.prototype.copywithin.title: Array.prototype.copyWithin()

sec-array.prototype.entries.name: entries
sec-array.prototype.entries.summary: The entries() method returns a new array iterator object that contains the key/value pairs for each index in the array.
sec-array.prototype.entries.title: Array.prototype.entries()

sec-array.prototype.every.name: every
sec-array.prototype.every.summary: The every() method tests whether all elements in the array pass the test implemented by the provided function. It returns a Boolean value.
sec-array.prototype.every.title: Array.prototype.every()

sec-array.prototype.fill.name: fill
sec-array.prototype.fill.summary: The fill() method changes all elements in an array to a static value, from a start index (default 0) to an end index (default array.length). It returns the modified array.
sec-array.prototype.fill.title: Array.prototype.fill()

sec-array.prototype.filter.name: filter
sec-array.prototype.filter.summary: The filter() method creates a shallow copy of a portion of a given array, filtered down to just the elements from the given array that pass the test implemented by the provided function.
sec-array.prototype.filter.title: Array.prototype.filter()

sec-array.prototype.find.name: find
sec-array.prototype.find.summary: The find() method returns the first element in the provided array that satisfies the provided testing function. If no values satisfy the testing function, undefined is returned.
sec-array.prototype.find.title: Array.prototype.find()

sec-array.prototype.findindex.name: findIndex
sec-array.prototype.findindex.summary: The findIndex() method returns the index of the first element in an array that satisfies the provided testing function. If no elements satisfy the testing function, -1 is returned.
sec-array.prototype.findindex.title: Array.prototype.findIndex()

sec-array.prototype.findlast.name: findLast
sec-array.prototype.findlast.summary: The findLast() method iterates the array in reverse order and returns the value of the first element that satisfies the provided testing function. If no elements satisfy the testing function, undefined is returned.
sec-array.prototype.findlast.title: Array.prototype.findLast()

sec-array.prototype.findlastindex.name: findLastIndex
sec-array.prototype.findlastindex.summary: The findLastIndex() method iterates the array in reverse order and returns the index of the first element that satisfies the provided testing function. If no elements satisfy the testing function, -1 is returned.
sec-array.prototype.findlastindex.title: Array.prototype.findLastIndex()

sec-array.prototype.flat.name: flat
sec-array.prototype.flat.summary: The flat() method creates a new array with all sub-array elements concatenated into it recursively up to the specified depth.
sec-array.prototype.flat.title: Array.prototype.flat()

sec-array.prototype.flatmap.name: flatMap
sec-array.prototype.flatmap.summary: The flatMap() method returns a new array formed by applying a given callback function to each element of the array, and then flattening the result by one level. It is identical to a map() followed by a flat() of depth 1 (arr.map(...args).flat()), but slightly more efficient than calling those two methods separately.
sec-array.prototype.flatmap.title: Array.prototype.flatMap()

sec-array.prototype.foreach.name: forEach
sec-array.prototype.foreach.summary: The forEach() method executes a provided function once for each array element.
sec-array.prototype.foreach.title: Array.prototype.forEach()

sec-array.from.name: from
sec-array.from.summary: The Array.from() static method creates a new, shallow-copied Array instance from an iterable or array-like object.
sec-array.from.title: Array.from()

sec-array.prototype.includes.name: includes
sec-array.prototype.includes.summary: The includes() method determines whether an array includes a certain value among its entries, returning true or false as appropriate.
sec-array.prototype.includes.title: Array.prototype.includes()

sec-array.prototype.indexof.name: indexOf
sec-array.prototype.indexof.summary: The indexOf() method returns the first index at which a given element can be found in the array, or -1 if it is not present.
sec-array.prototype.indexof.title: Array.prototype.indexOf()

sec-array.isarray.name: isArray
sec-array.isarray.summary: The Array.isArray() static method determines whether the passed value is an Array.
sec-array.isarray.title: Array.isArray()

sec-array.prototype.join.name: join
sec-array.prototype.join.summary: The join() method creates and returns a new string by concatenating all of the elements in an array (or an array-like object), separated by commas or a specified separator string. If the array has only one item, then that item will be returned without using the separator.
sec-array.prototype.join.title: Array.prototype.join()

sec-array.prototype.keys.name: keys
sec-array.prototype.keys.summary: The keys() method returns a new array iterator object that contains the keys for each index in the array.
sec-array.prototype.keys.title: Array.prototype.keys()

sec-array.prototype.lastindexof.name: lastIndexOf
sec-array.prototype.lastindexof.summary: The lastIndexOf() method returns the last index at which a given element can be found in the array, or -1 if it is not present. The array is searched backwards, starting at fromIndex.
sec-array.prototype.lastindexof.title: Array.prototype.lastIndexOf()

sec-properties-of-array-instances-length.name: length
sec-properties-of-array-instances-length.summary: The length data property of an Array instance represents the number of elements in that array. The value is an unsigned, 32-bit integer that is always numerically greater than the highest index in the array.
sec-properties-of-array-instances-length.title: Array: length

sec-array.prototype.map.name: map
sec-array.prototype.map.summary: The map() method creates a new array populated with the results of calling a provided function on every element in the calling array.
sec-array.prototype.map.title: Array.prototype.map()

sec-array.of.name: of
sec-array.of.summary: The Array.of() static method creates a new Array instance from a variable number of arguments, regardless of number or type of the arguments.
sec-array.of.title: Array.of()

sec-array.prototype.pop.name: pop
sec-array.prototype.pop.summary: The pop() method removes the last element from an array and returns that element. This method changes the length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.pop.title: Array.prototype.pop()

sec-array.prototype.push.name: push
sec-array.prototype.push.summary: The push() method adds the specified elements to the end of an array and returns the new length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.push.title: Array.prototype.push()

sec-array.prototype.reduce.name: reduce
sec-array.prototype.reduce.summary: The reduce() method executes a user-supplied "reducer" callback function on each element of the array, in order, passing in the return value from the calculation on the preceding element. The final result of running the reducer across all elements of the array is a single value.
sec-array.prototype.reduce.title: Array.prototype.reduce()

sec-array.prototype.reduceright.name: reduceRight
sec-array.prototype.reduceright.summary: The reduceRight() method applies a function against an accumulator and each value of the array (from right-to-left) to reduce it to a single value.
sec-array.prototype.reduceright.title: Array.prototype.reduceRight()

sec-array.prototype.reverse.name: reverse
sec-array.prototype.reverse.summary: The reverse() method reverses an array in place and returns the reference to the same array, the first array element now becoming the last, and the last array element becoming the first. In other words, elements order in the array will be turned towards the direction opposite to that previously stated.
sec-array.prototype.reverse.title: Array.prototype.reverse()

sec-array.prototype.shift.name: shift
sec-array.prototype.shift.summary: The shift() method removes the first element from an array and returns that removed element. This method changes the length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.shift.title: Array.prototype.shift()

sec-array.prototype.slice.name: slice
sec-array.prototype.slice.summary: The slice() method returns a shallow copy of a portion of an array into a new array object selected from start to end (end not included) where start and end represent the index of items in that array. The original array will not be modified.
sec-array.prototype.slice.title: Array.prototype.slice()

sec-array.prototype.some.name: some
sec-array.prototype.some.summary: The some() method tests whether at least one element in the array passes the test implemented by the provided function. It returns true if, in the array, it finds an element for which the provided function returns true; otherwise it returns false. It doesn't modify the array.
sec-array.prototype.some.title: Array.prototype.some()

sec-array.prototype.sort.name: sort
sec-array.prototype.sort.summary: The sort() method sorts the elements of an array in place and returns the reference to the same array, now sorted. The default sort order is ascending, built upon converting the elements into strings, then comparing their sequences of UTF-16 code units values.
sec-array.prototype.sort.title: Array.prototype.sort()

sec-array.prototype.splice.name: splice
sec-array.prototype.splice.summary: The splice() method changes the contents of an array by removing or replacing existing elements and/or adding new elements in place.

ie.notes: From Internet Explorer 5.5 through 8, all elements of the array will not be deleted if deleteCount is omitted. This behavior was fixed in Internet Explorer 9.

sec-array.prototype.splice.title: Array.prototype.splice()

sec-array.prototype.tolocalestring.name: toLocaleString
sec-array.prototype.tolocalestring.summary: The toLocaleString() method returns a string representing the elements of the array. The elements are converted to Strings using their toLocaleString methods and these Strings are separated by a locale-specific String (such as a comma ",").
sec-array.prototype.tolocalestring.title: Array.prototype.toLocaleString()

sec-array.prototype.toreversed.name: toReversed
sec-array.prototype.toreversed.summary: The toReversed() method of Array instances is the copying counterpart of the reverse() method. It returns a new array with the elements in reversed order.
sec-array.prototype.toreversed.title: Array.prototype.toReversed()

sec-array.prototype.tosorted.name: toSorted
sec-array.prototype.tosorted.summary: The toSorted() method of Array instances is the copying version of the sort() method. It returns a new array with the elements sorted in ascending order.
sec-array.prototype.tosorted.title: Array.prototype.toSorted()

sec-array.prototype.tospliced.name: toSpliced
sec-array.prototype.tospliced.summary: The toSpliced() method of Array instances is the copying version of the splice() method. It returns a new array with some elements removed and/or replaced at a given index.
sec-array.prototype.tospliced.title: Array.prototype.toSpliced()

sec-array.prototype.tostring.name: toString
sec-array.prototype.tostring.summary: The toString() method returns a string representing the specified array and its elements.
sec-array.prototype.tostring.title: Array.prototype.toString()

sec-array.prototype.unshift.name: unshift
sec-array.prototype.unshift.summary: The unshift() method adds the specified elements to the beginning of an array and returns the new length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.unshift.title: Array.prototype.unshift()

sec-array.prototype.values.name: values
sec-array.prototype.values.summary: The values() method returns a new array iterator object that iterates the value of each item in the array.

nodejs.notes: The --harmony-array-prototype-values flag is required; the --harmony flag is not sufficient in this case.

sec-array.prototype.values.title: Array.prototype.values()

sec-array.prototype.with.name: with
sec-array.prototype.with.summary: The with() method of Array instances is the copying version of using the bracket notation to change the value of a given index. It returns a new array with the element at the given index replaced with the given value.
sec-array.prototype.with.title: Array.prototype.with()

sec-array.prototype-@@iterator.name: @@iterator
sec-array.prototype-@@iterator.summary: The [@@iterator]() method of Array instances implements the iterable protocol and allows arrays to be consumed by most syntaxes expecting iterables, such as the spread syntax and for...of loops. It returns an array iterator object that yields the value of each index in the array.

firefox.notes: A placeholder property named @@iterator is used.
A placeholder property named iterator is used.

sec-array.prototype-@@iterator.title: Array.prototype[@@iterator]()

sec-get-array-@@species.name: @@species
sec-get-array-@@species.summary: The Array[@@species] static accessor property returns the constructor used to construct return values from array methods.
sec-get-array-@@species.title: Array[@@species]

sec-array.prototype-@@unscopables.name: @@unscopables
sec-array.prototype-@@unscopables.summary: The @@unscopables data property of Array.prototype is shared by all Array instances. It contains property names that were not included in the ECMAScript standard prior to the ES2015 version and that are ignored for with statement-binding purposes.
sec-array.prototype-@@unscopables.title: Array.prototype[@@unscopables]

sec-array-objects.name: Array
sec-array-objects.summary: The Array object, as with arrays in other programming languages, enables storing a collection of multiple items under a single variable name, and has members for performing common array operations.
sec-array-objects.title: Array

sec-arraybuffer-constructor.name: ArrayBuffer
sec-arraybuffer-constructor.summary: The ArrayBuffer() constructor creates ArrayBuffer objects.
sec-arraybuffer-constructor.title: ArrayBuffer() constructor

sec-get-arraybuffer.prototype.bytelength.name: byteLength
sec-get-arraybuffer.prototype.bytelength.summary: The byteLength accessor property of ArrayBuffer instances returns the length (in bytes) of this array buffer.
sec-get-arraybuffer.prototype.bytelength.title: ArrayBuffer.prototype.byteLength

sec-arraybuffer.isview.name: isView
sec-arraybuffer.isview.summary: The ArrayBuffer.isView() static method determines whether the passed value is one of the ArrayBuffer views, such as typed array objects or a DataView.
sec-arraybuffer.isview.title: ArrayBuffer.isView()

sec-arraybuffer.prototype.slice.name: slice
sec-arraybuffer.prototype.slice.summary: The slice() method returns a new ArrayBuffer whose contents are a copy of this ArrayBuffer's bytes from begin, inclusive, up to end, exclusive.

firefox.notes: The non-standard ArrayBuffer.slice() method has been removed in Firefox 53 (but the standardized version ArrayBuffer.prototype.slice() is kept.

sec-arraybuffer.prototype.slice.title: ArrayBuffer.prototype.slice()

sec-get-arraybuffer-@@species.name: @@species
sec-get-arraybuffer-@@species.summary: The ArrayBuffer[@@species] static accessor property returns the constructor used to construct return values from array buffer methods.
sec-get-arraybuffer-@@species.title: ArrayBuffer[@@species]

sec-arraybuffer-objects.name: ArrayBuffer
sec-arraybuffer-objects.summary: The ArrayBuffer object is used to represent a generic raw binary data buffer.
sec-arraybuffer-objects.title: ArrayBuffer

sec-async-function-constructor.name: AsyncFunction
sec-async-function-constructor.summary: The AsyncFunction() constructor creates AsyncFunction objects.
sec-async-function-constructor.title: AsyncFunction() constructor

sec-async-function-objects.name: AsyncFunction
sec-async-function-objects.summary: The AsyncFunction object provides methods for async functions. In JavaScript, every async function is actually an AsyncFunction object.
sec-async-function-objects.title: AsyncFunction

sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-next.name: next
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-next.summary: The next() method returns the next value in the sequence.
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-next.title: AsyncGenerator.prototype.next()

sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-return.name: return
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-return.summary: The return() method of AsyncGenerator instances acts as if a return statement is inserted in the generator's body at the current suspended position, which finishes the generator and allows the generator to perform any cleanup tasks when combined with a try...finally block.
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-return.title: AsyncGenerator.prototype.return()

sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-throw.name: throw
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-throw.summary: The throw() method of AsyncGenerator instances acts as if a throw statement is inserted in the generator's body at the current suspended position, which informs the generator of an error condition and allows it to handle the error, or perform cleanup and close itself.
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-throw.title: AsyncGenerator.prototype.throw()

sec-asyncgenerator-objects.name: AsyncGenerator
sec-asyncgenerator-objects.summary: The AsyncGenerator object is returned by an async generator function and it conforms to both the async iterable protocol and the async iterator protocol.
sec-asyncgenerator-objects.title: AsyncGenerator

sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-constructor.name: AsyncGeneratorFunction
sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-constructor.summary: The AsyncGeneratorFunction() constructor creates AsyncGeneratorFunction objects.
sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-constructor.title: AsyncGeneratorFunction() constructor

sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-objects.name: AsyncGeneratorFunction
sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-objects.summary: The AsyncGeneratorFunction object provides methods for async generator functions. In JavaScript, every async generator function is actually an AsyncGeneratorFunction object.
sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-objects.title: AsyncGeneratorFunction

sec-asynciteratorprototype-asynciterator.name: @@asyncIterator
sec-asynciteratorprototype-asynciterator.summary: The [@@asyncIterator]() method of AsyncIterator instances implements the async iterable protocol and allows built-in async iterators to be consumed by most syntaxes expecting async iterables, such as for await...of loops. It returns the value of this, which is the async iterator object itself.
sec-asynciteratorprototype-asynciterator.title: AsyncIterator.prototype[@@asyncIterator]()

sec-asynciteratorprototype.name: AsyncIterator
sec-asynciteratorprototype.summary: An AsyncIterator object is an object that conforms to the async iterator protocol by providing a next() method that returns a promise fulfilling to an iterator result object. The AsyncIterator.prototype object is a hidden global object that all built-in async iterators inherit from. It provides an @@asyncIterator method that returns the async iterator object itself, making the async iterator also async iterable.
sec-asynciteratorprototype.title: AsyncIterator

sec-atomics.add.name: add
sec-atomics.add.summary: The Atomics.add() static method adds a given value at a given position in the array and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.add.title: Atomics.add()

sec-atomics.and.name: and
sec-atomics.and.summary: The Atomics.and() static method computes a bitwise AND with a given value at a given position in the array, and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.and.title: Atomics.and()

sec-atomics.compareexchange.name: compareExchange
sec-atomics.compareexchange.summary: The Atomics.compareExchange() static method exchanges a given replacement value at a given position in the array, if a given expected value equals the old value. It returns the old value at that position whether it was equal to the expected value or not. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.compareexchange.title: Atomics.compareExchange()

sec-atomics.exchange.name: exchange
sec-atomics.exchange.summary: The Atomics.exchange() static method stores a given value at a given position in the array and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens between the read of the old value and the write of the new value.
sec-atomics.exchange.title: Atomics.exchange()

sec-atomics.islockfree.name: isLockFree
sec-atomics.islockfree.summary: The Atomics.isLockFree() static method is used to determine whether the Atomics methods use locks or atomic hardware operations when applied to typed arrays with the given element byte size. It returns false if the given size is not one of the BYTES_PER_ELEMENT property of integer TypedArray types.
sec-atomics.islockfree.title: Atomics.isLockFree()

sec-atomics.load.name: load
sec-atomics.load.summary: The Atomics.load() static method returns a value at a given position in the array.
sec-atomics.load.title: Atomics.load()

sec-atomics.notify.name: notify
sec-atomics.notify.summary: The Atomics.notify() static method notifies up some agents that are sleeping in the wait queue.
sec-atomics.notify.title: Atomics.notify()

sec-atomics.or.name: or
sec-atomics.or.summary: The Atomics.or() static method computes a bitwise OR with a given value at a given position in the array, and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.or.title: Atomics.or()

sec-atomics.store.name: store
sec-atomics.store.summary: The Atomics.store() static method stores a given value at the given position in the array and returns that value.
sec-atomics.store.title: Atomics.store()

sec-atomics.sub.name: sub
sec-atomics.sub.summary: The Atomics.sub() static method subtracts a given value at a given position in the array and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.sub.title: Atomics.sub()

sec-atomics.wait.name: wait
sec-atomics.wait.summary: The Atomics.wait() static method verifies that a shared memory location still contains a given value and if so sleeps, awaiting a wake-up notification or times out. It returns a string which is either "ok", "not-equal", or "timed-out".
sec-atomics.wait.title: Atomics.wait()

sec-atomics.waitasync.name: waitAsync
sec-atomics.waitasync.summary: The Atomics.waitAsync() static method waits asynchronously on a shared memory location and returns a Promise.
sec-atomics.waitasync.title: Atomics.waitAsync()

sec-atomics.xor.name: xor
sec-atomics.xor.summary: The Atomics.xor() static method computes a bitwise XOR with a given value at a given position in the array, and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.xor.title: Atomics.xor()

sec-atomics-object.name: Atomics
sec-atomics-object.summary: The Atomics namespace object contains static methods for carrying out atomic operations. They are used with SharedArrayBuffer and ArrayBuffer objects.

safari.notes: Before Safari 16.4, Atomics is gated behind COOP/COEP. For more detail, read Making your website "cross-origin isolated" using COOP and COEP.

sec-atomics-object.title: Atomics

sec-bigint-constructor.name: BigInt
sec-bigint-constructor.summary: The BigInt() function returns primitive values of type BigInt.
sec-bigint-constructor.title: BigInt() constructor

sec-bigint.asintn.name: asIntN
sec-bigint.asintn.summary: The BigInt.asIntN() static method truncates a BigInt value to the given number of least significant bits and returns that value as a signed integer.
sec-bigint.asintn.title: BigInt.asIntN()

sec-bigint.asuintn.name: asUintN
sec-bigint.asuintn.summary: The BigInt.asUintN() static method truncates a BigInt value to the given number of least significant bits and returns that value as an unsigned integer.
sec-bigint.asuintn.title: BigInt.asUintN()

sec-bigint.prototype.tostring.name: toString
sec-bigint.prototype.tostring.summary: The toString() method returns a string representing the specified BigInt value. The trailing "n" is not part of the string.
sec-bigint.prototype.tostring.title: BigInt.prototype.toString()

sec-bigint.prototype.valueof.name: valueOf
sec-bigint.prototype.valueof.summary: The valueOf() method returns the wrapped primitive value of a BigInt object.
sec-bigint.prototype.valueof.title: BigInt.prototype.valueOf()

sec-bigint-objects.name: BigInt
sec-bigint-objects.summary: BigInt values represent numeric values which are too large to be represented by the number primitive.
sec-bigint-objects.title: BigInt

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: BigInt64Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The BigInt64Array() constructor creates BigInt64Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0n.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: BigInt64Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: BigUint64Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The BigUint64Array() constructor creates BigUint64Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0n.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: BigUint64Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Float32Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Float32Array() constructor creates Float32Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Float32Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Float64Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Float64Array() constructor creates Float64Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Float64Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Int16Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Int16Array() constructor creates Int16Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Int16Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Int32Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Int32Array() constructor creates Int32Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Int32Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Int8Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Int8Array() constructor creates Int8Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Int8Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint16Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint16Array() constructor creates Uint16Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint16Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint32Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint32Array() constructor creates Uint32Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint32Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint8Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint8Array() constructor creates Uint8Array objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint8Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint8ClampedArray
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint8ClampedArray() constructor creates Uint8ClampedArray objects. The contents are initialized to 0.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint8ClampedArray() constructor

sec-typedarray-objects.name: BigInt64Array
sec-typedarray-objects.summary: The BigInt64Array typed array represents an array of 64-bit signed integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0n. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or by using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-objects.title: BigInt64Array

sec-typedarray-objects.name: BigUint64Array
sec-typedarray-objects.summary: The BigUint64Array typed array represents an array of 64-bit unsigned integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0n. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or by using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-objects.title: BigUint64Array

sec-typedarray-objects.name: TypedArray
sec-typedarray-objects.summary: A TypedArray object describes an array-like view of an underlying binary data buffer. There is no global property named TypedArray, nor is there a directly visible TypedArray constructor. Instead, there are a number of different global properties, whose values are typed array constructors for specific element types, listed below. On the following pages you will find common properties and methods that can be used with any typed array containing elements of any type.
sec-typedarray-objects.title: TypedArray

sec-boolean-constructor.name: Boolean
sec-boolean-constructor.summary: The Boolean() constructor creates Boolean objects. When called as a function, it returns primitive values of type Boolean.

safari_ios.notes: Also supported in Safari for iOS 4.2, but not on DOM objects.

sec-object.defineproperty.title: Object.defineProperty()

sec-object.entries.name: entries
sec-object.entries.summary: The Object.entries() static method returns an array of a given object's own enumerable string-keyed property key-value pairs.
sec-object.entries.title: Object.entries()

sec-object.freeze.name: freeze
sec-object.freeze.summary: The Object.freeze() static method freezes an object. Freezing an object prevents extensions and makes existing properties non-writable and non-configurable. A frozen object can no longer be changed: new properties cannot be added, existing properties cannot be removed, their enumerability, configurability, writability, or value cannot be changed, and the object's prototype cannot be re-assigned. freeze() returns the same object that was passed in.
sec-object.freeze.title: Object.freeze()

sec-object.fromentries.name: fromEntries
sec-object.fromentries.summary: The Object.fromEntries() static method transforms a list of key-value pairs into an object.
sec-object.fromentries.title: Object.fromEntries()

sec-object.getownpropertydescriptor.name: getOwnPropertyDescriptor
sec-object.getownpropertydescriptor.summary: The Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor() static method returns an object describing the configuration of a specific property on a given object (that is, one directly present on an object and not in the object's prototype chain). The object returned is mutable but mutating it has no effect on the original property's configuration.

ie.notes: In Internet Explorer 8, this was only supported on DOM objects and with some non-standard behaviors. This was later fixed in Internet Explorer 9.

sec-object.getownpropertydescriptor.title: Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor()

sec-object.getownpropertydescriptors.name: getOwnPropertyDescriptors
sec-object.getownpropertydescriptors.summary: The Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptors() static method returns all own property descriptors of a given object.
sec-object.getownpropertydescriptors.title: Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptors()

sec-object.getownpropertynames.name: getOwnPropertyNames
sec-object.getownpropertynames.summary: The Object.getOwnPropertyNames() static method returns an array of all properties (including non-enumerable properties except for those which use Symbol) found directly in a given object.
sec-object.getownpropertynames.title: Object.getOwnPropertyNames()

sec-object.getownpropertysymbols.name: getOwnPropertySymbols
sec-object.getownpropertysymbols.summary: The Object.getOwnPropertySymbols() static method returns an array of all symbol properties found directly upon a given object.
sec-object.getownpropertysymbols.title: Object.getOwnPropertySymbols()

sec-object.getprototypeof.name: getPrototypeOf
sec-object.getprototypeof.summary: The Object.getPrototypeOf() static method returns the prototype (i.e. the value of the internal [[Prototype]] property) of the specified object.
sec-object.getprototypeof.title: Object.getPrototypeOf()

sec-object.hasown.name: hasOwn
sec-object.hasown.summary: The Object.hasOwn() static method returns true if the specified object has the indicated property as its own property. If the property is inherited, or does not exist, the method returns false.
sec-object.hasown.title: Object.hasOwn()

sec-object.prototype.hasownproperty.name: hasOwnProperty
sec-object.prototype.hasownproperty.summary: The hasOwnProperty() method returns a boolean indicating whether the object has the specified property as its own property (as opposed to inheriting it).
sec-object.prototype.hasownproperty.title: Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()

sec-object.is.name: is
sec-object.is.summary: The Object.is() static method determines whether two values are the same value.
sec-object.is.title: Object.is()

sec-object.isextensible.name: isExtensible
sec-object.isextensible.summary: The Object.isExtensible() static method determines if an object is extensible (whether it can have new properties added to it).
sec-object.isextensible.title: Object.isExtensible()

sec-object.isfrozen.name: isFrozen
sec-object.isfrozen.summary: The Object.isFrozen() static method determines if an object is frozen.
sec-object.isfrozen.title: Object.isFrozen()

sec-object.prototype.isprototypeof.name: isPrototypeOf
sec-object.prototype.isprototypeof.summary: The isPrototypeOf() method checks if an object exists in another object's prototype chain.
sec-object.prototype.isprototypeof.title: Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()

sec-object.issealed.name: isSealed
sec-object.issealed.summary: The Object.isSealed() static method determines if an object is sealed.
sec-object.issealed.title: Object.isSealed()

sec-object.keys.name: keys
sec-object.keys.summary: The Object.keys() static method returns an array of a given object's own enumerable string-keyed property names.
sec-object.keys.title: Object.keys()

sec-object.preventextensions.name: preventExtensions
sec-object.preventextensions.summary: The Object.preventExtensions() static method prevents new properties from ever being added to an object (i.e. prevents future extensions to the object). It also prevents the object's prototype from being re-assigned.
sec-object.preventextensions.title: Object.preventExtensions()

sec-object.prototype.propertyisenumerabl.name: propertyIsEnumerable
sec-object.prototype.propertyisenumerabl.summary: The propertyIsEnumerable() method returns a boolean indicating whether the specified property is the object's enumerable own property.
sec-object.prototype.propertyisenumerabl.title: Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()

sec-object.seal.name: seal
sec-object.seal.summary: The Object.seal() static method seals an object. Sealing an object prevents extensions and makes existing properties non-configurable. A sealed object has a fixed set of properties: new properties cannot be added, existing properties cannot be removed, their enumerability and configurability cannot be changed, and its prototype cannot be re-assigned. Values of existing properties can still be changed as long as they are writable. seal() returns the same object that was passed in.
sec-object.seal.title: Object.seal()

sec-object.setprototypeof.name: setPrototypeOf
sec-object.setprototypeof.summary: The Object.setPrototypeOf() static method sets the prototype (i.e., the internal [[Prototype]] property) of a specified object to another object or null.
sec-object.setprototypeof.title: Object.setPrototypeOf()

sec-object.prototype.tolocalestring.name: toLocaleString
sec-object.prototype.tolocalestring.summary: The toLocaleString() method returns a string representing the object. This method is meant to be overridden by derived objects for locale-specific purposes.
sec-object.prototype.tolocalestring.title: Object.prototype.toLocaleString()

sec-object.prototype.tostring.name: toString
sec-object.prototype.tostring.summary: The toString() method returns a string representing the object. This method is meant to be overridden by derived objects for custom type conversion logic.
sec-object.prototype.tostring.title: Object.prototype.toString()

sec-object.prototype.valueof.name: valueOf
sec-object.prototype.valueof.summary: The valueOf() method of Object instances converts the this value to an object. This method is meant to be overridden by derived objects for custom type conversion logic.
sec-object.prototype.valueof.title: Object.prototype.valueOf()

sec-object.values.name: values
sec-object.values.summary: The Object.values() static method returns an array of a given object's own enumerable string-keyed property values.
sec-object.values.title: Object.values()

sec-object-objects.name: Object
sec-object-objects.summary: The Object type represents one of JavaScript's data types. It is used to store various keyed collections and more complex entities. Objects can be created using the Object() constructor or the object initializer / literal syntax.
sec-object-objects.title: Object

sec-promise-constructor.name: Promise
sec-promise-constructor.summary: The Promise() constructor creates Promise objects. It is primarily used to wrap callback-based APIs that do not already support promises.

firefox.notes: Constructor requires a new operator since version 37.

nodejs.notes: Constructor requires a new operator since version 4.

safari.notes: Constructor requires a new operator since version 10.

sec-promise-constructor.title: Promise() constructor

sec-promise.all.name: all
sec-promise.all.summary: The Promise.all() static method takes an iterable of promises as input and returns a single Promise. This returned promise fulfills when all of the input's promises fulfill (including when an empty iterable is passed), with an array of the fulfillment values. It rejects when any of the input's promises rejects, with this first rejection reason.
sec-promise.all.title: Promise.all()

sec-promise.allsettled.name: allSettled
sec-promise.allsettled.summary: The Promise.allSettled() static method takes an iterable of promises as input and returns a single Promise. This returned promise fulfills when all of the input's promises settle (including when an empty iterable is passed), with an array of objects that describe the outcome of each promise.
sec-promise.allsettled.title: Promise.allSettled()

sec-promise.any.name: any
sec-promise.any.summary: The Promise.any() static method takes an iterable of promises as input and returns a single Promise. This returned promise fulfills when any of the input's promises fulfills, with this first fulfillment value. It rejects when all of the input's promises reject (including when an empty iterable is passed), with an AggregateError containing an array of rejection reasons.
sec-promise.any.title: Promise.any()

sec-promise.prototype.catch.name: catch
sec-promise.prototype.catch.summary: The catch() method of Promise instances schedules a function to be called when the promise is rejected. It immediately returns an equivalent Promise object, allowing you to chain calls to other promise methods. It is a shortcut for Promise.prototype.then(undefined, onRejected).
sec-promise.prototype.catch.title: Promise.prototype.catch()

sec-promise.prototype.finally.name: finally
sec-promise.prototype.finally.summary: The finally() method of Promise instances schedules a function to be called when the promise is settled (either fulfilled or rejected). It immediately returns an equivalent Promise object, allowing you to chain calls to other promise methods.
sec-promise.prototype.finally.title: Promise.prototype.finally()

sec-promise.race.name: race
sec-promise.race.summary: The Promise.race() static method takes an iterable of promises as input and returns a single Promise. This returned promise settles with the eventual state of the first promise that settles.
sec-promise.race.title: Promise.race()

sec-promise.reject.name: reject
sec-promise.reject.summary: The Promise.reject() static method returns a Promise object that is rejected with a given reason.
sec-promise.reject.title: Promise.reject()

sec-promise.resolve.name: resolve
sec-promise.resolve.summary: The Promise.resolve() static method "resolves" a given value to a Promise. If the value is a promise, that promise is returned; if the value is a thenable, Promise.resolve() will call the then() method with two callbacks it prepared; otherwise the returned promise will be fulfilled with the value.
sec-promise.resolve.title: Promise.resolve()

sec-promise.prototype.then.name: then
sec-promise.prototype.then.summary: The then() method of Promise instances takes up to two arguments: callback functions for the fulfilled and rejected cases of the Promise. It immediately returns an equivalent Promise object, allowing you to chain calls to other promise methods.
sec-promise.prototype.then.title: Promise.prototype.then()

sec-get-promise-@@species.name: @@species
sec-get-promise-@@species.summary: The Promise[@@species] static accessor property returns the constructor used to construct return values from promise methods.
sec-get-promise-@@species.title: Promise[@@species]

sec-promise-objects.name: Promise
sec-promise-objects.summary: The Promise object represents the eventual completion (or failure) of an asynchronous operation and its resulting value.
sec-promise-objects.title: Promise

sec-proxy-constructor.name: Proxy
sec-proxy-constructor.summary: The Proxy() constructor creates Proxy objects.
sec-proxy-constructor.title: Proxy() constructor

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: apply
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.apply() method is a trap for the [[Call]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as function calls.
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.apply()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: construct
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.construct() method is a trap for the [[Construct]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as the new operator. In order for the new operation to be valid on the resulting Proxy object, the target used to initialize the proxy must itself be a valid constructor.
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.construct()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: defineProperty
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.defineProperty() method is a trap for the [[DefineOwnProperty]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as Object.defineProperty().
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.defineProperty()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: deleteProperty
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.deleteProperty() method is a trap for the [[Delete]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as the delete operator.
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.deleteProperty()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: get
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.get() method is a trap for the [[Get]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as property accessors.
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.get()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: getOwnPropertyDescriptor
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.getOwnPropertyDescriptor() method is a trap for the [[GetOwnProperty]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor().
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.getOwnPropertyDescriptor()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: getPrototypeOf
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.getPrototypeOf() method is a trap for the [[GetPrototypeOf]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as Object.getPrototypeOf().
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.getPrototypeOf()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: has
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.has() method is a trap for the [[HasProperty]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as the in operator.
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.has()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: isExtensible
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.isExtensible() method is a trap for the [[IsExtensible]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as Object.isExtensible().
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.isExtensible()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: ownKeys
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.ownKeys() method is a trap for the [[OwnPropertyKeys]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as Object.keys(), Reflect.ownKeys(), etc.

firefox.notes: In Firefox 42, the implementation got updated to reflect the final ES2015 specification: The result is now checked if it is an array and if the array elements are either of type string or of type symbol. Enumerating duplicate own property names is not a failure anymore.

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.ownKeys()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: preventExtensions
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.preventExtensions() method is a trap for the [[PreventExtensions]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as Object.preventExtensions().
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.preventExtensions()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: set
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.set() method is a trap for the [[Set]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as using property accessors to set a property's value.
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.set()

sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.name: setPrototypeOf
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.summary: The handler.setPrototypeOf() method is a trap for the [[SetPrototypeOf]] object internal method, which is used by operations such as Object.setPrototypeOf().
sec-proxy-object-internal-methods-and-in.title: handler.setPrototypeOf()

sec-proxy.revocable.name: revocable
sec-proxy.revocable.summary: The Proxy.revocable() static method creates a revocable Proxy object.
sec-proxy.revocable.title: Proxy.revocable()

sec-proxy-objects.name: Proxy
sec-proxy-objects.summary: The Proxy object enables you to create a proxy for another object, which can intercept and redefine fundamental operations for that object.
sec-proxy-objects.title: Proxy

sec-native-error-types-used-in-this-stan.name: RangeError
sec-native-error-types-used-in-this-stan.summary: The RangeError object indicates an error when a value is not in the set or range of allowed values.
sec-native-error-types-used-in-this-stan.title: RangeError

sec-native-error-types-used-in-this-stan.name: ReferenceError
sec-native-error-types-used-in-this-stan.summary: The ReferenceError object represents an error when a variable that doesn't exist (or hasn't yet been initialized) in the current scope is referenced.
sec-native-error-types-used-in-this-stan.title: ReferenceError

sec-reflect.apply.name: apply
sec-reflect.apply.summary: The Reflect.apply() static method calls a target function with arguments as specified.
sec-reflect.apply.title: Reflect.apply()

sec-reflect.construct.name: construct
sec-reflect.construct.summary: The Reflect.construct() static method is like the new operator, but as a function. It is equivalent to calling new target(...args). It gives also the added option to specify a different new.target value.
sec-reflect.construct.title: Reflect.construct()

sec-reflect.defineproperty.name: defineProperty
sec-reflect.defineproperty.summary: The Reflect.defineProperty() static method is like Object.defineProperty() but returns a Boolean.
sec-reflect.defineproperty.title: Reflect.defineProperty()

sec-reflect.deleteproperty.name: deleteProperty
sec-reflect.deleteproperty.summary: The Reflect.deleteProperty() static method is like the delete operator, but as a function. It deletes a property from an object.
sec-reflect.deleteproperty.title: Reflect.deleteProperty()

sec-reflect.get.name: get
sec-reflect.get.summary: The Reflect.get() static method is like the property accessor syntax, but as a function.
sec-reflect.get.title: Reflect.get()

sec-reflect.getownpropertydescriptor.name: getOwnPropertyDescriptor
sec-reflect.getownpropertydescriptor.summary: The Reflect.getOwnPropertyDescriptor() static method is like Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(). It returns a property descriptor of the given property if it exists on the object, undefined otherwise.
sec-reflect.getownpropertydescriptor.title: Reflect.getOwnPropertyDescriptor()

sec-reflect.getprototypeof.name: getPrototypeOf
sec-reflect.getprototypeof.summary: The Reflect.getPrototypeOf() static method is like Object.getPrototypeOf(). It returns the prototype of the specified object.
sec-reflect.getprototypeof.title: Reflect.getPrototypeOf()

sec-reflect.has.name: has
sec-reflect.has.summary: The Reflect.has() static method is like the in operator, but as a function.
sec-reflect.has.title: Reflect.has()

sec-reflect.isextensible.name: isExtensible
sec-reflect.isextensible.summary: The Reflect.isExtensible() static method is like Object.isExtensible(). It determines if an object is extensible (whether it can have new properties added to it).
sec-reflect.isextensible.title: Reflect.isExtensible()

sec-reflect.ownkeys.name: ownKeys
sec-reflect.ownkeys.summary: The Reflect.ownKeys() static method returns an array of the target object's own property keys.
sec-reflect.ownkeys.title: Reflect.ownKeys()

sec-reflect.preventextensions.name: preventExtensions
sec-reflect.preventextensions.summary: The Reflect.preventExtensions() static method is like Object.preventExtensions(). It prevents new properties from ever being added to an object (i.e., prevents future extensions to the object).
sec-reflect.preventextensions.title: Reflect.preventExtensions()

sec-reflect.set.name: set
sec-reflect.set.summary: The Reflect.set() static method is like the property accessor and assignment syntax, but as a function.
sec-reflect.set.title: Reflect.set()

sec-reflect.setprototypeof.name: setPrototypeOf
sec-reflect.setprototypeof.summary: The Reflect.setPrototypeOf() static method is like Object.setPrototypeOf() but returns a Boolean. It sets the prototype (i.e., the internal [[Prototype]] property) of a specified object.
sec-reflect.setprototypeof.title: Reflect.setPrototypeOf()

sec-reflect-object.name: Reflect
sec-reflect-object.summary: The Reflect namespace object contains static methods for invoking interceptable JavaScript object internal methods. The methods are the same as those of proxy handlers.
sec-reflect-object.title: Reflect

sec-regexp-constructor.name: RegExp
sec-regexp-constructor.summary: The RegExp() constructor creates RegExp objects.
sec-regexp-constructor.title: RegExp() constructor

sec-get-regexp.prototype.dotAll.name: dotAll
sec-get-regexp.prototype.dotAll.summary: The dotAll accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the s flag is used with this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.dotAll.title: RegExp.prototype.dotAll

sec-regexp.prototype.exec.name: exec
sec-regexp.prototype.exec.summary: The exec() method executes a search for a match in a specified string and returns a result array, or null.
sec-regexp.prototype.exec.title: RegExp.prototype.exec()

sec-get-regexp.prototype.flags.name: flags
sec-get-regexp.prototype.flags.summary: The flags accessor property of RegExp instances returns the flags of this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.flags.title: RegExp.prototype.flags

sec-get-regexp.prototype.global.name: global
sec-get-regexp.prototype.global.summary: The global accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the g flag is used with this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.global.title: RegExp.prototype.global

sec-get-regexp.prototype.hasIndices.name: hasIndices
sec-get-regexp.prototype.hasIndices.summary: The hasIndices accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the d flag is used with this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.hasIndices.title: RegExp.prototype.hasIndices

sec-get-regexp.prototype.ignorecase.name: ignoreCase
sec-get-regexp.prototype.ignorecase.summary: The ignoreCase accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the i flag is used with this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.ignorecase.title: RegExp.prototype.ignoreCase

sec-properties-of-regexp-instances.name: lastIndex
sec-properties-of-regexp-instances.summary: The lastIndex data property of a RegExp instance specifies the index at which to start the next match.
sec-properties-of-regexp-instances.title: RegExp: lastIndex

sec-get-regexp.prototype.multiline.name: multiline
sec-get-regexp.prototype.multiline.summary: The multiline accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the m flag is used with this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.multiline.title: RegExp.prototype.multiline

sec-get-regexp.prototype.source.name: source
sec-get-regexp.prototype.source.summary: The source accessor property of RegExp instances returns a string containing the source text of this regular expression, without the two forward slashes on both sides or any flags.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.source.title: RegExp.prototype.source

sec-get-regexp.prototype.sticky.name: sticky
sec-get-regexp.prototype.sticky.summary: The sticky accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the y flag is used with this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.sticky.title: RegExp.prototype.sticky

sec-regexp.prototype.test.name: test
sec-regexp.prototype.test.summary: The test() method executes a search for a match between a regular expression and a specified string. Returns true if there is a match; false otherwise.
sec-regexp.prototype.test.title: RegExp.prototype.test()

sec-regexp.prototype.tostring.name: toString
sec-regexp.prototype.tostring.summary: The toString() method returns a string representing the regular expression.
sec-regexp.prototype.tostring.title: RegExp.prototype.toString()

sec-get-regexp.prototype.unicode.name: unicode
sec-get-regexp.prototype.unicode.summary: The unicode accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the u flag is used with this regular expression.

sec-get-regexp.prototype.unicode.title: RegExp.prototype.unicode

sec-get-regexp.prototype.unicodesets.name: unicodeSets
sec-get-regexp.prototype.unicodesets.summary: The unicodeSets accessor property of RegExp instances returns whether or not the v flag is used with this regular expression.
sec-get-regexp.prototype.unicodesets.title: RegExp.prototype.unicodeSets

sec-regexp.prototype-@@match.name: @@match
sec-regexp.prototype-@@match.summary: The [@@match]() method of RegExp instances specifies how String.prototype.match() should behave. In addition, its presence (or absence) can influence whether an object is regarded as a regular expression.

sec-regexp-prototype-matchall.name: @@matchAll
sec-regexp-prototype-matchall.summary: The [@@matchAll]() method of RegExp instances specifies how String.prototype.matchAll should behave.
sec-regexp-prototype-matchall.title: RegExp.prototype[@@matchAll]()

sec-regexp.prototype-@@replace.name: @@replace
sec-regexp.prototype-@@replace.summary: The [@@replace]() method of RegExp instances specifies how String.prototype.replace() and String.prototype.replaceAll() should behave when the regular expression is passed in as the pattern.

sec-regexp.prototype-@@search.name: @@search
sec-regexp.prototype-@@search.summary: The [@@search]() method of RegExp instances specifies how String.prototype.search should behave.
sec-regexp.prototype-@@search.title: RegExp.prototype[@@search]()

sec-get-regexp-@@species.name: @@species
sec-get-regexp-@@species.summary: The RegExp[@@species] static accessor property returns the constructor used to construct copied regular expressions in certain RegExp methods.
sec-get-regexp-@@species.title: RegExp[@@species]

sec-regexp.prototype-@@split.name: @@split
sec-regexp.prototype-@@split.summary: The [@@split]() method of RegExp instances specifies how String.prototype.split should behave when the regular expression is passed in as the separator.
sec-regexp.prototype-@@split.title: RegExp.prototype[@@split]()

sec-regexp-regular-expression-objects.name: RegExp
sec-regexp-regular-expression-objects.summary: The RegExp object is used for matching text with a pattern.

sec-set-constructor.name: Set
sec-set-constructor.summary: The Set() constructor creates Set objects.
sec-set-constructor.title: Set() constructor

sec-set.prototype.add.name: add
sec-set.prototype.add.summary: The add() method inserts a new element with a specified value in to a Set object, if there isn't an element with the same value already in the Set.
sec-set.prototype.add.title: Set.prototype.add()

sec-set.prototype.clear.name: clear
sec-set.prototype.clear.summary: The clear() method removes all elements from a Set object.
sec-set.prototype.clear.title: Set.prototype.clear()

sec-set.prototype.delete.name: delete
sec-set.prototype.delete.summary: The delete() method removes a specified value from a Set object, if it is in the set.
sec-set.prototype.delete.title: Set.prototype.delete()

sec-set.prototype.entries.name: entries
sec-set.prototype.entries.summary: The entries() method returns a new set iterator object that contains an array of [value, value] for each element in the Set object, in insertion order.
